<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-14T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-14T04:00:00-05:00" n="536" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d536">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">852.2221 Dahl, Harold/61: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Seville</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bay</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Seville</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-14T10:00:00+01:00">September 14, 1937—10
                                    a.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 14—6:34 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Referring to your [<hi rend="italic">my?</hi>] telegram of September 13
                                [<hi rend="italic">12?</hi>], 10 a.m. Letter just received from
                            General Queipo de Llano states that General Franco declares that Dahl
                            has not been condemned to death but has been placed on the list of
                            prisoners to be exchanged.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bay</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>